subic:
It seems that the code does not include the cssnano the documentation implies. You will have to add your own css compressor. You can for example manually add cssnano to your vue-loader-config postcss processors. 
build/vue-loader-config.js
module.exports = {
   ...
  postcss: [
    require('autoprefixer')({
      browsers: ['last 2 versions']
    }),
    require('cssnano')() //add this
  ]
}
Requiring the cssnano (and installing it with npm install cssnano --save-dev) in postcss options will now compress your production CSS when running build. You can also pass the cssnano options as an object (same as with the autoprefixer above).
See also:
- Vue loader PostCSS docs
- cssnano
EDIT: For an alternative solution see the submitted pull request #484 using optimize-css-assets-webpack-plugin..

